      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DID SO (8) should enjoy clear running from the outside box. Below best latest at Ballarat (25.89) when 6th and beaten 6 lengths. Goes very well at course and distance boasting three wins. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Should be very hard to beat this time. NEVERMIND (1) was never in contention last time after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 1.75 lengths at this track (22.91) beating Jay's Girl in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 on June 30. In the mix. VINNIE BLACK (2) was well in the market last time but only managed fifth (23.11), beaten 4 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from six attempts. One of the better chances. ASTON PASTIZZI (7) is a last-start placegetter worth considering.",
